The paper focuses on the development of a static analysis framework for Ethereum smart contracts, which involves program analysis techniques like dataflow and taint tracking. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the categories of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), Software Engineering (cs.SE), Programming Languages (cs.PL), Systems and Control (cs.SY), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). However, since the paper primarily deals with the security aspects of smart contracts, cs.CR is the most likely category, followed by cs.SE and cs.PL.
